The paper discusses the security and privacy concerns associated with IoT, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves the use of blockchain technology, which is a distributed system (cs.DC) and involves the use of smart contracts, which is a software engineering concept (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the performance overheads associated with the proposed approach, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS).
